### ENVIRONMENT Variables - VERCEL_SKEW_PROTECTION_ENABLED, VERCEL_URL

Source: https://github.com/vercel/vercel/blob/main/packages/functions/docs/modules/index.md

Describes environment variables exposed to Vercel functions relevant to skew protection and deployment URL. These are read-only variables provided by the platform and used at runtime inside serverless functions.

```APIDOC
## ENVIRONMENT VERCEL_* variables

### Description
Platform-provided environment variables available to functions. They convey deployment URL and skew protection status. These are not callable endpoints but runtime variables used by functions.

### Method
N/A

### Endpoint
Environment Variables (available at runtime)

### Parameters
#### Path Parameters
- **None**

#### Query Parameters
- **None**

#### Request Body
- **None**

### Variables
- **VERCEL_SKEW_PROTECTION_ENABLED** (string | undefined) - Optional - Set to "1" when Skew Protection is enabled in Project Settings.
- **VERCEL_URL** (string | undefined) - Optional - The domain of the generated deployment URL without protocol (e.g., "my-app.vercel.app"). Note: cannot be used with Standard Deployment Protection.

### Request Example
{
  "example_access": "const url = process.env.VERCEL_URL"
}

### Response
#### Success Response (200)
- **N/A** - This documents runtime variables; not an HTTP response.

#### Response Example
{
  "VERCEL_SKEW_PROTECTION_ENABLED": "1",
  "VERCEL_URL": "my-app.vercel.app"
}

```

