### POST /purge/src - invalidateBySrcImage

Source: https://github.com/vercel/vercel/blob/main/packages/functions/docs/modules/index.md

Invalidate cached resources by source image path(s). Call this when you need to purge CDN cache entries corresponding to one or more image source paths.

```APIDOC
## POST /purge/src

### Description
Invalidate cached content by providing one or more source image paths. This helper returns a Promise that resolves when the purge request is dispatched.

### Method
POST

### Endpoint
/purge/src

### Parameters
#### Path Parameters
- **None** (no path parameters)

#### Query Parameters
- **None**

#### Request Body
- **src** (string | string[]) - Required - Single source path or an array of source paths to invalidate.

### Request Example
{
  "src": "/images/photo-123.jpg"
}

### Response
#### Success Response (200)
- **void** - The function returns a Promise that resolves with no value once the purge is initiated.

#### Response Example
{
  "status": "purge_requested",
  "items": ["/images/photo-123.jpg"]
}

```

