### Run integration tests locally - Shell (bash)

Source: https://github.com/vercel/vercel/blob/main/README.md

Commands to set environment variables, change to the package directory, and run a specific integration test. Dependencies: pnpm, node, and a valid VERCEL_TOKEN and VERCEL_TEAM_ID exported into your shell. Input: none beyond previously created token/team ID; Output: test runner output; Limitation: full integration suite is discouraged locally — prefer isolating a single test.

```bash
echo 'export VERCEL_TOKEN=<MY-TOKEN> VERCEL_TEAM_ID=<MY-TEAM-ID>' >> ~/.zshrc
```

```bash
cd packages/next
pnpm test test/fixtures/00-server-build/index.test.js
```

```bash
cd ./packages/node
pnpm build
npm pack
vercel *.tgz
# Then edit your project's vercel.json to replace "use" with the returned URL
