### Extend Request Handler Lifetime with waitUntil (JavaScript)

Source: https://github.com/vercel/vercel/blob/main/packages/functions/docs/modules/index.md

The `waitUntil` function extends the lifetime of a request handler in Vercel Edge Functions, allowing background tasks to complete even after a response has been sent to the client. It takes a Promise as an argument and ensures the function remains active until that Promise settles. This is useful for non-critical operations like logging, analytics, or cache updates.

```JavaScript
import { waitUntil } from '@vercel/functions';

export function GET(request) {
  waitUntil(fetch('https://vercel.com'));
  return new Response('OK');
}
```

