### Check Rate Limit for Vercel API Route (TypeScript)

Source: https://github.com/vercel/vercel/blob/main/packages/firewall/README.md

This TypeScript snippet demonstrates how to use `@vercel/firewall`'s `checkRateLimit` function within an API route to enforce programmatic rate limits. It checks if the current request is rate-limited based on a unique identifier and returns a 429 status code if so, preventing further processing of the request.

```typescript
