### Create bootstrap that invokes Lambda runtime wrapper (bash)

Source: https://github.com/vercel/vercel/blob/main/DEVELOPING_A_RUNTIME.md

Bootstrap examples that show how to invoke a runtime wrapper when AWS_LAMBDA_EXEC_WRAPPER is set and how to replace the bootstrap process with exec. Dependencies: bash shell and the AWS_LAMBDA_EXEC_WRAPPER environment variable. Inputs: wrapper path and runtime command/parameters; Outputs: wrapper process takes over the runtime. Limitation: unsetting vs setting to blank can behave differently; use exec/execve to replace the process.

```bash
#!/bin/bash

exec $AWS_LAMBDA_EXEC_WRAPPER path/to/runtime param1 param2

```

```bash
#!/bin/bash

if [[ -n $AWS_LAMBDA_EXEC_WRAPPER ]]
  __WRAPPER=$AWS_LAMBDA_EXEC_WRAPPER
  AWS_LAMBDA_EXEC_WRAPPER=""
  exec $__WRAPPER "$0" "${@}"
fi

# start the actual runtime functionality

```

